#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:1
msgid "Dashboard Scripts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:4
msgid ""
"This page documents how to use the VTK `dashboard` branch in [Git][]. See "
"the [README](README.md) for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:9
msgid "Using the Dashboard Scripts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:12
msgid ""
"The `dashboard` branch contains a dashboard client helper script. Use these "
"commands to track it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:15
msgid ""
"$ mkdir -p ~/Dashboards/VTKScripts\n"
"$ cd ~/Dashboards/VTKScripts\n"
"$ git init\n"
"$ git remote add -t dashboard origin https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk.git\n"
"$ git pull origin\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:21
msgid ""
"The `vtk_common.cmake` script contains setup instructions in its top "
"comments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:24
msgid ""
"Update the `dashboard` branch to get the latest version of this script by "
"simply running:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:27
msgid "$ git pull\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:29
msgid "Here is a link to the script as it appears today: [vtk_common.cmake][]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:33
msgid "Changing the Dashboard Scripts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:36
msgid ""
"If you find bugs in the hooks themselves or would like to add new features, "
"the can be edited in the usual Git manner:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:39
msgid "$ git checkout -b my-topic-branch\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:41
msgid ""
"Make your edits, test it, and commit the result.  Create a patch file with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:43
msgid "$ git format-patch origin/dashboard\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/dashboard.md:45
msgid ""
"And post the results in the [Development][] category in the [VTK Discourse]"
"[] forum."
msgstr ""
